{"blocks":[{"key":"2tbn9","text":"Add PBS, K-citrate, MgSO4 to a 1 L bottle and fill to 1 L with milliQ water. Adjust pH to 6.5 (about 50 μl of 6N 
HCl or about 100 μl of 2N HCl). Leave a stirring bar inside the bottle. 



","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6npl3","text":"Check the mass of all tubes, tare the heaviest one, and add PPBS to the others to equalize weight (within a 0.1 g 
margin of error). 



","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d17li","text":"If DNAse treating samples, resuspend pellet in 100 μl of 0.02 μm filtered UltraPure water into a labeled 2 mL 
microcentrifuge tube. Set heat block to 37°C. 



","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":3,"length":22}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4p1f9","text":"(1)  No DNase step: Scrape pellet from ultracentrifuge tube and place in bead tube. Take 100 μl of CD1, which is already in bead tube, and use it to resuspend whatever is left of the pellet and put into bead tube. 
","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":5,"length":13}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8b57v","text":"(2)  DNase step: After stop solution has been added, transfer resuspended pellet to bead tube. 



","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":5,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
